DOC_LEVEL: L2
MODULE: runtime/pipeline-infra
PATH: src/pipeline-infra/**
DESCRIPTION: shared infrastructure contract layer for pipeline config, paths, errors, and script execution

KEY_FILES:
- src/pipeline-infra/index.js
- src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js
- src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js
- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js
- src/pipeline-infra/cli-entry.js
- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js
- src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js
- src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js

PYTHON_MIRROR: dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py
PARITY_TESTS: tests/pipeline-infra/path-policy-python-compat.test.js
UNIT_TESTS:
- tests/pipeline-infra/error-codes.test.js
- tests/pipeline-infra/config-loader.test.js
- tests/pipeline-infra/path-policy.test.js
- tests/pipeline-infra/cli-entry.test.js
- tests/pipeline-infra/script-runner.test.js
- tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js
- tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js
INTEGRATION_TESTS:
- tests/integration/f001-infrastructure.integration.test.js

PUBLIC_APIS:
- loadPipelineInfraConfig(input?) -> normalized pipeline config + defaults
- loadAndValidateConfig(input?) -> { ok, config?, errors? } batch validation
- EXIT_CODES -> { SUCCESS: 0, RUNTIME_ERROR: 1, USAGE_ERROR: 2, TIMEOUT: 124 }
- DIRECTORY_CONVENTION -> frozen canonical directory layout object
- resolvePlansPaths(projectRoot) -> { plansDir }
- createCliEntry(options) -> { run, config, logger, flags, positionalArgs }
- computeFeatureSlug(featureId, title)
- resolveFeaturePaths({ projectRoot, featureId, title, sessionId })
- resolveBugPaths({ projectRoot, bugId, sessionId })
- resolveDaemonLogPaths(projectRoot)
- resolveLockPaths(projectRoot) -> F-004 lock file paths
- resolveLastResultPaths(projectRoot) -> F-004 last result paths
- resolveDaemonMetaPaths(projectRoot) -> F-004 daemon meta paths
- resolvePipelineStatePaths(projectRoot) -> F-004 pipeline state paths
- resolveCurrentSessionPaths(projectRoot) -> F-004 current session paths
- getStatePaths(projectRoot, type) -> F-004 all state paths for type
- executePipelineCommand(req)
- buildPipelineCommand(req, config) -> { command, args }
- createLockManager(options?) -> F-004 lock manager instance
- createStateManager(options?) -> F-004 state manager instance

SERVICE_LAYER: src/services/pipeline-control-service.js
SERVICE_TESTS: tests/services/pipeline-control-service.test.js

ERROR_MODEL:
- codes: CONFIG_MISSING, CONFIG_INVALID, PATH_INVALID, SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND, EXEC_TIMEOUT, EXEC_FAILED, CLI_USAGE_ERROR, CLI_UNKNOWN_ARG
- F-004 codes: LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED, ALREADY_STOPPED, PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING, INVALID_TARGET, TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE, DAEMON_START_FAILED
- createInfraError(code, message, { hint, context }) -> serializable infra error payload

TRAPS:
- keep path_policy.py and path-policy.js behavior aligned (slug + session paths + daemon logs)
- avoid breaking existing run.sh/run-bugfix.sh CLI contracts
- request validation must reject unknown pipelineType/action and missing targetId for retry/reset
- lock files must use atomic write (temp file + rename) to prevent corruption
- PID validation must check process alive with process.kill(pid, 0) + ESRCH catch

DECISIONS:
- 2026-03-10 | f001-js-path-policy | include explicit daemon log policy resolver for US2 coverage
- 2026-03-10 | f001-runner-actions | treat logs/reset as first-class runner actions for US3 coverage
- 2026-03-12 | f001-feature-complete | all US1-US4 acceptance criteria verified via integration tests
- 2026-03-12 | f004-lock-manager | file lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (D1)
- 2026-03-12 | f004-state-manager | separate module for state file management (D2)
- 2026-03-12 | f001-v2-batch-config | add loadAndValidateConfig for batch error collection (US-1)
- 2026-03-12 | f001-v2-directory-convention | add DIRECTORY_CONVENTION constant and resolvePlansPaths (US-2)
- 2026-03-12 | f001-v2-cli-entry | add createCliEntry reusable wrapper with EXIT_CODES (US-3)
- 2026-03-12 | f001-v2-tooling-baseline | expand tsconfig to src/**/*.js, add eslint rules baseline (US-4)
